  <h3>Point of the Game</h3>
  <div>
    <p>The object of the game is to win the most rounds by playing a noun from one's hand to best &quot;match&quot; that round's communal adjective, which will be decided by the Judge.</p>
  </div>
  <h3>Game Rules</h3>
  <div>
     <p><ul>
      <li>One judge per round.</li>
      <li>Judges will rotate throughout the table</li>
      <li>Each player must have a hand of 7 nouns or noun phrases at all times.  These nouns are only visible to their respective player.</li>
      <li>Only the judge can decide which matches best with the adjective.</li>
      <li>The adjective will be randomly selected by the system.</li>
      <li>Each player except for the judge will select a noun.</li>
      <li>The player who submitted the noun will not be visible to the judge.</li>
      <li>The selected noun is the winner of the round.</li>
      <li>The player who has submitted the nouns will be revealed after judgement.</li>
      <li>A new noun will be distributed to each player after every noun played.</li>
      <li>Players are not allowed to hint at their cards to persuade the Judge.
    </ul></p>
  </div>
